<p>One key iteration that occurred through the user tests was ensure the final product page was one that would optimise conversions to the company website - this was a key goal of both the user and business owners. I found through the user testing, user's were unsure what action to take next once they had reached the product page. For example, many found the contact information on the product page and explained that from there, may call or ‘google’ the company to purchase the product and/or service. 
To ensure this page led to conversions, I built in clear key buttons which would direct the user to the company’s webpages with ease. When testing this feature with users again, it proved to reduce confusion and increased click throughs to the company website. </p>
